1 D. The provisions of this section shall preempt any ordinance,
2 regulation, or restriction that was lawfully adopted or license that
3 was issued by a political subdivision of this state prior to the
4 effective date of this act that is in conflict with the provisions
5 of this section.
6 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
